      • iter

        public static java.util.Iterator iter(Functor next)
        This method creates an iterator over a given function object.

        Equivalence: iter(next, null, null).

        The returned iterator will not support the remove() method.

        Parameters:
        next - is the function object that is invoked by the iterator's next() method.
        Returns:
        an iterator that simply invokes the given function object.

      • iter

        public static java.util.Iterator iter(Functor next,
                      Functor has)
        This method creates an iterator over a pair of function objects.

        Equivalence: iter(next, has, null).

        The returned iterator will not support the remove() method.

        Parameters:
        next - is the function object that is invoked by the iterator's next() method.
        has - is the function object that is invoked by the iterator's hasNext() method.
        Returns:
        an iterator based on the given function objects.

      • iter

        public static java.util.Iterator iter(Functor next,

                      Functor remove)
        This method creates an iterator over a pair of function objects.

        has - is the function object that is invoked by the iterator's hasNext() method.
